#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
fitgrab — FitGirl Repacks downloader via FuckingFast mirrors.

Usage:
    fitgrab <url> --dir ~/Games
    fitgrab <url> --dry-run

Full pipeline (all stages run headless Chromium — no requests/BS4 needed):

  Stage 1 — fitgirl game page
      Load the page, find the anchor labelled "Filehoster: FuckingFast",
      grab its href (a PrivateBin paste URL).

  Stage 2 — PrivateBin paste page  ← WHY Playwright is required here
      The paste URL is:  https://paste.fitgirl-repacks.site/?<id>#<key>
      The #fragment is a client-side AES key. The server returns encrypted
      JSON; the page's own JS decrypts it using the key and renders the links.
      requests gets back ciphertext. Playwright runs the JS, waits for the
      decrypted <a> tags to appear, then reads them.

  Stage 3 — FuckingFast per-file pages  ← WHY page.expect_download() here
      Click 1: JS opens an ad popup + sets a local "visited" flag.
               We close the popup immediately.
      Click 2: Flag is set → JS triggers a file download (stays on same page).
      The download URL has NO .rar extension — it's an opaque CDN path.
      Route-based interception on file extensions therefore misses it.
      page.expect_download() fires on *any* download regardless of URL shape.
      We capture the URL from the download object, then cancel it.
      aria2c handles the actual bytes.

  Stage 4 — aria2c
      3 concurrent files × 4 connections each. Resume-safe.

Rate-limit bypass strategy (Stage 3):
  - Per-context UA + viewport rotation: each tab looks like a distinct visitor.
  - Full-jitter exponential backoff: spreads retry load instead of spiking it.
  - Persistent retry queue: failed URLs re-enter the pipeline with attempt
    counters carried forward, so backoff widens globally not just per-tab.
  - Worker cooldown on hard 429s: pauses the worker before re-queuing,
    giving the CDN's sliding window time to clear.
"""

